## Auto-Discovery Mode (Optional Enhancement)

When a student heartbeats from a PC that isn't in `lab_computers` yet, the system can:
1. **Still resolve the lab** via `lab_gateways` (gateway IP → lab name) ✅
2. Log an "unknown PC" entry with the raw hostname
3. Admin/teacher still sees `PC1 — Laboratory 2` even without pre-configuration
4. Admin can optionally add a display name later

This means the system works **even if admin hasn't pre-configured all PCs** — just the gateway table needs to be filled.

---

## Database Schema (Final)

```
lab_gateways            lab_computers                  monitoring_sessions
─────────────           ─────────────────              ──────────────────────
id                      id                             ...
gateway_ip (unique)     hostname                       computer_name
laboratory_room         display_name                   gateway_ip
description             laboratory_room                laboratory_room (cached)
                        [UNIQUE: hostname+lab_room]    last_heartbeat
```

---

## Summary of New API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Who | Purpose |
|---|---|---|---|
| GET | `/api/lab-gateways` | Admin, Teacher | List all gateway→lab mappings |
| POST | `/api/lab-gateways` | Admin | Add a new lab gateway |
| PATCH | `/api/lab-gateways/{id}` | Admin | Update lab gateway |
| DELETE | `/api/lab-gateways/{id}` | Admin | Remove lab gateway |

*(Existing lab-computers endpoints are updated, not replaced)*

